The paper focuses on improving the performance of CNN models on sentence classification tasks by studying desirable properties such as semantic coherence, attention mechanism, and reusability. These properties are relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computer vision (cs.CV). However, given the focus on sentence classification tasks and the use of Word2Vec representation and SentiWordNet, cs.CL is the most likely sub-category.
